summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling its previous resolutions and statements concerning the situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo,
Encouraged by progress in the peace process since the Global and All Inclusive Agreement in December 2002,
Notes that reform of the security sector, including disarmament, demobilization and reintegration (DDR) of former combatants, is key to the transition process,
Reaffirms overall responsibility lies with the Government of National Unity and Transition,
 Welcomes efforts to set up an integrated brigade in Kisangani as a step towards a comprehensive programme for a Congolese integrated national army;
2. Decides that the demand for demilitarization of Kisangani in resolution 1304 (2000) shall not apply to restructured and integrated Congolese forces;
3. Urges the Government to take measures for restructuring and integration of armed forces, including setting up a Supreme Defence Council and a national plan for DDR;
4. Calls upon the international community to provide assistance for integration and restructuring of armed forces;
5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
